rComments: This prof is very enthusiast about the course, however, the material is hard, and the way he explains it makes it even harder. This prof is approachable and attempts to clarify questions but it's very complicated to understand.
classes are boring because material is not explained well. he is generally a nice teacher but kind of monotone when presenting material to class

He made the course super hard, that none of us can even pass the homework grade. The homework is also super difficult that we couldn't even understand and comprehend. The most important thing is, he only reads through slides, and just keeps on talking about the examples that you don't even know.

I attempted to take this class for god knows what reason and although i emailed the professor on numerous occasions it took him THREE weeks to respond and his response was very unhelpful and extremely rude. This professor is a prime example of what a bad professor is, i am glad i  was saved from taking what i imagine to be a torturous class.
slow, boring, not helpful and always drifts off  topic. Worst prof ever!
He makes the course more difficult than it should be
so dull.

very condescending manner, does not want to take the time to address students concerns, highly unorganized.  I felt he has too many things on the go and this class was not at all a priority. He often forgets what has been covered in class, many errors on assignments and exams which are corrected by other students.  Very disappointed!
Worst prof ever...  very mean.. very rude...go home binnick...!!
soooo dull

Good prof.

Binnick is a good prof. He obviously knows his field inside and out, but his style of delivery is not conductive to picking up the information.  I did the redings and hw and still hard a hard time following.  More explanation for lectures, less history.

Its a good class, boring yes, but linguitics isn't exactly pop culture phenomena, its a tiresome discipline, yet he explains it clearly. Read the text - simple as that. If you dont understand, drop the class and don't waste his or your time.

I love it whenever he give examples of other people's languages. He does it very well, and as for his teachings....definately we must do the readings before class. The TAs however, gets me very confused,...and that's the reason why I left.

No one should be complaining, the midterm was a piece of cake, and if you didn't think so I guess you just didn't put the effort in. If you do the reading before class, you know exactly what he's talking about. The students are the problem, not the prof

binnick... you gotta realize not everyone in the class is a linguist.. in fact, we're all in first year! so please, be more clear and stop spending half the lecture to explain a useless concept and the other to make important info even harder 2understand!
